000/$0.25, or 40,000 meters of fiber.&nbsp; This would be about 1.1 kilomet=
ers of cable that has 36 fibers in it.&nbsp; Obviously, even the smallest c=
ountry would use enough fiber to justify obtaining a patent.<br clear=3D"no=
